Permanent Secretary, State House, Jalal Arabi, has urged Nigerians to disregard publications indicating that the State House Clinic is currently recruiting A statement by the State House Director of Information, Attah Esa, urges the public to ignore notices of recruitment at State House Clinic currently making the rounds on the internet. The statement said the â€œPermanent Secretary advises the public to be more circumspect and wary of such notices that are designed by mischief makers to deceive and extort unsuspecting job seekers. Arabi assured that the sponsors of the publication will be investigated and prosecuted.  Tony Ailemen, Abuja